either converted into organized matter in the<lb/>
parts of living vegetables or they are decomposed<lb/>
and changed in consequence of their Chemical<lb/>
agencies. -<lb/>
The least durable of the manures are<lb/>
those that most immediately supply nourishment<lb/>
to the plant sooner or later they are decomposed<lb/>
and partily assimilated to its organs and the soil<lb/>
becomes exhausted of them -<lb/>
The manures which increase vegetation<lb/>
merely by their agencies are the substances<lb/>
contained in soils are more permanent<lb/>
But even they are continually modified<lb/>
at the time that they exert their powers<lb/>
and at length are converted into new<lb/>
